r for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Elizabeth FitzEllis was born about 1292, in Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom, her father, William Fitz Ellis IV, was 14 and her mother, Isabel de la Beche, was 15. She married John Russell in 1309, in Strensham, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter. She died in 1363, at the age of 72."},"et":{"about 1292–1363":"umbes 1292–1363","1292–1363":"1292–1363","1290–1363":"1290–1363","1309–Male":"1309–Surnud","1314–1376":"1314–1376","1315–1363":"1315–1363","1318–1376":"1318–1376","1279–1318":"1279–1318","1279–Female":"1279–Surnud","1315":"1315","1314":"1314","about 1292":"umbes 1292","1279":"1279","1376":"1376","after 1309":"pärast 1309","Bef 1315":"enne 1315","1363":"1363","1309":"1309","1292":"1292","1318":"1318","1290":"1290","Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Corston, Wiltshire, Eng.":"Corston, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Strensham, Worcestershire, England":"Strensham, Worcestershire, England","Worcester, Worcestershire, England":"Worcester, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1292–1363":"noin 1292–1363","1292–1363":"1292–1363","1290–1363":"1290–1363","1309–Male":"1309–Kuollut","1314–1376":"1314–1376","1315–1363":"1315–136